              <dd>Bronze</dd>
            
           
                        <dt>Technique</dt>
             <dd>Cast, lost-wax process</dd>
           
                          <dt>Dimensions</dt>
              <dd>13 x 1 cm (5 1/8 x 3/8 in.)</dd>
            
                          <dt>Technical Details</dt>
              <dd>
                                                      <p class="divider">Chemical Composition: XRF data from Tracer<br />
Alloy: Bronze<br />
Alloying Elements: copper, tin<br />
Other Elements: lead, iron, nickel, arsenic<br />
K. Eremin, January 2014</p>
                                      <p class="divider">Technical Observations: The patina on the obverse shows warty green corrosion with occasional inclusions of blue azurite. There are tan-brown encrustations from burial. The reverse has brownish, slightly over cleaned surfaces with patches of green malachite and red cuprite.<br />
 <br />
The mirror is missing its handle, fragments from the lower edge, and the lower part of the medallion. Two fragments have been reattached, and two blind cracks are present: one around the rim and one into the medallion. <br />
 <br />
The mirror was cast with the notched edge as part of the casting. Designs on the reverse were done by cold working.<br />
 <br />
 <br />
Carol Snow and Nina Vinogradskaya (submitted 2002)</p>
                                                </dd>
            
            
            
            
            
